Package: TopDom
===============

Version: 0.1.1-9000 [2018-06-07]

NOTE:

 o The license of the underlying TopDom R code/scripts is still unknown,
   i.e. to be decided by the original authors of TopDom.  Any mentioning
   of code licenses in this package / git repository history is invalid.
   
NEW FEATURES:

 o Add overlapScores().

 o Add image() for TopDomData.
 
 o List returned by TopDom() gained class 'TopDom'.

 o Added logical option 'TopDom.debug', which controls whether functions
   produce debug output or not.  The default is FALSE.

DOCUMENTATION:

 o Updated the 'Value' section of help("TopDom") with details from the
   TopDom Manual (an online PDF) provided by Shin et al.
 

Version: 0.1.1 [2018-05-04]

NEW FEATURES:

 o Add print() method for TopDomData object.

 o Reference the TopDom paper (Shin et al., 2016) in the help and the README.
 

Version: 0.1.0 [2018-04-23]

SIGNIFICANT CHANGES:

 o Turned the original TopDom R script into a package.

 o All progress messages are outputted done to standard error.

 o Add readHiC().

NEW FEATURES:

 o TopDom() can now read, via readHiC(), a pure count matrix file without bin
   information.  To read such files, specify what chromosome is being read
   (argument 'chr') and the bin size of the count matrix (argument 'binSize').

 o If the matrix file is not of a known format, then TopDom() produces an
   informative error. Previously it gave a message on stdout and returned 0.

CODE STYLE:

 o Tidied up code.

SOFTWARE QUALITY:

 o Added package tests.
 

Version: 0.0.2 [2016-07-08]

 o TopDom v0.0.2 script from http://zhoulab.usc.edu/TopDom/ with the below
   entries from the official release note:
   
 o Gap Identification module is changed.
   
 o Minor bug related to Change Points identificaiton in very small
   regions is fixed.
     
 o bed format support.
   

Version: 0.0.1 [2015-11-09]

 o TopDom v0.0.1 script from http://zhoulab.usc.edu/TopDom/.
